TITLE: Asynchronous Controller Testing with Database Isolation in Loco-rs
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to test controllers asynchronously with isolated database contexts. This approach creates a random database schema for each test to prevent test interference and cleans up after completion, ensuring test reliability.
SOURCE: https://github.com/loco-rs/loco/blob/master/docs-site/content/docs/the-app/controller.md#2025-04-20_snippet_49

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use loco_rs::testing::prelude::*;

#[tokio::test]
async fn can_print_echo() {
    configure_insta!();

    request_with_create_db::<App, _, _>(|request, _ctx| async move {
        let response = request
            .post("/example")
            .json(&serde_json::json!({"site": "Loco"}))
            .await;

        assert_debug_snapshot!((response.status_code(), response.text()));
    })
    .await;
}
```

