TITLE: Creating a Table Migration in Loco-rs
DESCRIPTION: Implementing a migration that creates a new table with columns. This example creates a 'posts' table with title and content columns and implements both up and down migrations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/loco-rs/loco/blob/master/docs-site/content/docs/the-app/models.md#2025-04-20_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
impl MigrationTrait for Migration {
    async fn up(&self, m: &SchemaManager) -> Result<(), DbErr> {
        create_table(
            m,
            "posts",
            &[
                ("title", ColType::StringNull),
                ("content", ColType::StringNull),
            ],
            &[],
        )
        .await
    }

    async fn down(&self, m: &SchemaManager) -> Result<(), DbErr> {
        drop_table(m, "posts").await
    }
}
```

