TITLE: Implementing a Backup Strategy for Storage Redundancy
DESCRIPTION: Configures a backup storage strategy that provides redundancy across multiple storage providers with a specific failure mode policy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/loco-rs/loco/blob/master/docs-site/content/docs/infrastructure/storage.md#2025-04-20_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
// Define the backup strategy by setting the primary store and secondary stores by names.
let strategy: Box<dyn StorageStrategy> = Box::new(BackupStrategy::new(
    "store_1",
    Some(vec!["store_2".to_string(), "store_3".to_string()]),
    FailureMode::AllowBackupFailure,
)) as Box<dyn StorageStrategy>;

let storage = Storage::new(
    BTreeMap::from([
        ("store_1".to_string(), store_1),
        ("store_2".to_string(), store_2),
        ("store_3".to_string(), store_3),
    ]),
    strategy.into(),
);
```

