TITLE: Setting up Application Load Balancer in Terraform
DESCRIPTION: Creates an Application Load Balancer (ALB) to route traffic to the ECS service, configuring it with public subnets and security groups for HTTP and HTTPS traffic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/loco-rs/loco/blob/master/docs-site/content/blog/deploy-aws.md#2025-04-20_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: hcl
CODE:
```
resource "aws_alb" "myapp" {
  name               = "myapp-lb"
  internal           = false
  load_balancer_type = "application"
  enable_deletion_protection = true

  subnets = [
    aws_subnet.public_d.id,
    aws_subnet.public_e.id,
  ]

  security_groups = [
    aws_security_group.http.id,
    aws_security_group.https.id,
    aws_security_group.egress_all.id,
  ]

  depends_on = [aws_internet_gateway.igw]
}
```

